ol.li: when the key sess:{user_id}-{hash} expires or gets deleted, db0 sends a message __keyevent@0__:<expired | del> sess:{user_id}-{hash};
the Sandbox Broker service subscribes to __keyevent@0__:expired and __keyevent@0__:del events;

li.span: when it receives a message, catches the user_id fragment from the key;

ol.li: after that, fetches the value of the key user:{user_id} in db1;

li.span: knowing cNodePoolId, cNodeId, host, protocol and port of the sandbox, it makes the request:
DELETE http://{host}/sandboxes/{user_id} to the cnode hosted in the host address. This will:
remove the key user:{user_id} from db1;
push the port as the last element of the array stored in the nested key
